1. There’s an Object.assign function that copies all properties from one object into another.
Object.assign

2.The trim method removes whitespace (spaces, newlines, tabs, and similar characters)
from the start and end of a string.

/*
3.A string can be repeated with the repeat method, which creates a new string 
containing multiple copies of the original string, glued together.
*/

4.It can be useful for a function to accept any number of arguments. For example, Math.max 
computes the maximum of all the arguments it is given.
To write such a function, you put three dots before the function’s last parameter, like this: